description: Five doctors and two nurses from France and Switzerland who carried out several humanitarian missions in Gaza since November 2023 spoke to Le Monde about the impossibility of meeting the population's needs and how the experience left a lasting mark on them.

description: As Benjamin Netanyahu convened a security council meeting on Tuesday, Israeli media discussed the possibility of a larger, even total, occupation of the enclave. This would be a turning point with far-reaching consequences.

headline: Lake Chad residents caught between Boko Haram and rising waters
description: 'Lake Chad's Troubled Waters' (1/4). Contrary to popular belief, the lake is not disappearing but expanding, to the dismay of residents already facing jihadist attacks. Confronted with the effects of climate change, they are organizing to better manage agricultural spaces.

headline: Greece is becoming better equipped to fight wildfires
description: After hiring new firefighters and purchasing additional aircraft and drones, the country has reported a 34% decrease in burned areas since the start of 2025.

headline: French man arrested in Slovenia for crimes committed in Croatia during 1991 war
description: A French citizen originally from the former Yugoslavia has been imprisoned for three months and is facing extradition to Croatia. His lawyers condemned this as a violation of his rights. His family members in France fear 'revenge' for contested events.

headline: Sydney Sweeney's American Eagle ad sparks controversy online and pleases Donald Trump
description: With a slogan playing on the ambiguity between 'genes' and 'jeans' − 'Sydney Sweeney has great jeans' − the actress has sparked controversy. Some have accused her of promoting eugenics, while President Donald Trump has come to American Eagle's defense, triggering a surge in its stock price.

headline: Mariia Nazarenko's first days in France after fleeing Ukraine: 'In Kyiv, I was a university professor. Today, I am a refugee searching for toothpaste'
description: On February 21, 2022, Nazarenko left Ukraine, thinking it was just for a weekend. The next day, Russia invaded her country. A few days later, she found herself in Lyon. Now 40 years old, she lives in Paris.
